# Parameterized Tests

Run the same test with different inputs!

## Real World Scenario

Testing a login form with one user isn't enough. You need to test valid users, locked users, invalid formats, and empty fields. Parameterized tests let you write the logic once and run it against dozens of data points.

## Test.each Pattern

```javascript
const testCases = [
    { input: 'hello', expected: 'HELLO' },
    { input: 'world', expected: 'WORLD' },
];

for (const { input, expected } of testCases) {
    // Run test with each data set
    await page.fill('#input', input);
    await page.click('#uppercase');
    const result = await page.locator('#output').textContent();
    console.log(result === expected ? 'PASS' : 'FAIL');
}
```

## Your Task
1. Define test data for 3 calculations
2. Loop through and verify each
3. Return count of passed tests

