# CSV Test Data

Tabular data for comprehensive testing!

## Real World Scenario

Business analysts often work with spreadsheets. Using CSV data sources allows non-technical team members to define test cases (inputs and expected outputs) that your automation script can simply execute.

## Parse CSV

```javascript
const csv = `name,email,expected
Alice,alice@test.com,Welcome Alice
Bob,bob@test.com,Welcome Bob`;

const rows = csv.split('\n').slice(1);
const data = rows.map(row => {
    const [name, email, expected] = row.split(',');
    return { name, email, expected };
});
```

## Benefits

- Easy to edit in spreadsheets
- Non-technical friendly
- Bulk test cases

## Your Task
1. Parse the CSV data
2. Test with the second row
3. Return the welcome message

